mdps.katex.mathDelimiters:
Delimiters of katex mathï¼Œformat is {"left": "chars", "right": "chars"}; Multiple delimiters are separated by ',', example: {"left": "$", "right": "$"},{"left": "\(", "right": "\)"}; Default value is an empty string, it means that the internal default value is used.

The internal default values of each attribute are as follows:
The default value of latexinline is { "left": "$", "right": "$" },{ "left": "\\(", "right": "\\)" }
The default value of latexdisplay is { "left": "$$", "right": "$$" },{ "left": "\\[", "right": "\\]" }
The default value of asciiinline is { "left": "@ ", "right": " @" },{ "left": "~ ", "right": " ~" }
The default value of asciidisplay is { "left": "@@", "right": "@@" }
